## Development setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env           # edit SECRET_KEY at minimum
make install                   # install dependencies
uv run pre-commit install      # set up git hooks (run once)
{% if use_postgres or use_worker -%}
make services                  # start external services (Docker required)
{% endif -%}
{% if use_postgres -%}
make migrate                   # apply migrations (first run and after new migrations)
{% endif -%}
make dev                       # start server at http://localhost:8000
```

{% if use_postgres or use_worker %}
`make services` starts {% if use_postgres %}Postgres{% endif %}{% if use_postgres and use_worker %} and {% endif %}{% if use_worker %}Redis{% endif %} in the background via Docker Compose. `make dev` calls this automatically, but running it first lets you confirm the services are healthy before starting the app.
{% endif %}

Open `http://localhost:8000/docs` to explore the API (only available when `DEBUG=true`).

